[[File:Roger_Christian_George_Lucas.png|thumb|300px|Roger Christian with George Lucas on the set of ''The Phantom Menace'']]
'''Roger Christian''' (born [[February 25]], [[1940s#1944|1944]]) was the set decorator for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] and the second unit director for both [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] (the former of which was uncredited).<ref name="SWCA">{{WebCite|url=http://theswca.com/index.php?action=disp_item&item_id=77834|text=Revenge of the Jedi Call Sheet (Ewok Village)|archivedate=20160305110443}}</ref> In [[1978]] he won the [[Wikipedia:Academy Award for Best Production Design|Academy Award for Best Production Design]] for his work on ''A New Hope''. He also directed [[Wikipedia:Black Angel (1980 film)|''Black Angel'']], a short film that was shown before the theatrical release of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] in certain locales. Christian later indicated in a 2014 interview that he was the third crew member to actually be cast for the project.<ref name="Esquire">{{WebCite|url=http://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/a28570/star-wars-roger-christian|text=The Man Who Literally Built 'Star Wars'|author=Singer, Jeremy|date=2014-05-04|archivedate=20150221184145}}</ref>

Outside of ''Star Wars'', Roger has also done second unit direction for one of the ''Young Indiana Jones'' movie compilations, done art direction for ''Alien'' and ''Life of Brian'' and directed the critically despised film ''Battlefield Earth''.<ref name="Shadowlocked">{{WebCite|url=http://www.shadowlocked.com/201203212466/opinion-features/roger-christian-talks-zombies-prometheus-battlefield-earth.html|text=Roger Christian talks zombies, Prometheus &amp; Battlefield Earth|author=Anderson, Martin|date=2012-03-21|archivedate=20160315051840}}</ref>

